  <summary date="2024-08-13T20:33:07Z" status="Introduced in House">Helping Emergency Responders Overcome Act or the HERO Act

This bill establishes a series of programs relating to the behavioral health of law enforcement officers, first responders, 9-1-1 operators, and other public safety officers and health care providers.

The programs include

a public safety officer suicide-reporting system at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention,a grant program for peer-support behavioral health and wellness programs within fire departments and emergency medical services agencies, anda grant program for behavioral health and wellness programs for health care providers.</summary>
